+# Implementation Summary
+
+## Claims Applied
+
+### C1 — Remove Duplicate Proactive Permissions Comment
+**File**: `packages/core/src/sandbox/utils/proactivePermissions.ts`
+Deleted the duplicate JSDoc block above `getProactiveToolSuggestions`, leaving a single copy.
+
+### C2 — Centralize Command Name Normalization
+**File**: `packages/core/src/sandbox/utils/proactivePermissions.ts`
+Added private `normalizeCommandName(commandName: string): string` helper. Replaced inline `.toLowerCase().replace(/\.exe$/, '')` in both `isNetworkReliantCommand` and `getProactiveToolSuggestions` with calls to the new helper.
+
+### C3 — Align Proactive Confirmation Comments With Actual Tool Scope
+**File**: `packages/core/src/tools/shell.ts`
+Updated three comments (lines ~249, ~353, ~718) that referred narrowly to "Node.js ecosystem tools" or "network-heavy tools (npm install, etc.)" to say "known network-reliant tools" — matching the actual tool set (git, ssh, curl, wget, plus package managers).
+
+### C4 — Build Execution Additional Permissions Through a Local Merge
+**File**: `packages/core/src/tools/shell.ts`
+Extracted the inline permissions merge (network + fileSystem read/write from both `PARAM_ADDITIONAL_PERMISSIONS` and `proactivePermissionsConfirmed`) into a local `additionalPermissions` variable computed before the `ShellExecutionService.execute` call, then passed that variable into the service options.
+
+## Files Modified
